{"key":"post-9804540","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9804540</id>\n<content>The steam conducts heat through the glass into the substrate.&amp;nbsp; It does not penetrate the holes.&amp;nbsp; Begin timing your 90 minutes when the steam begins to escape from under the tight fitting lid.&amp;nbsp; This will be about ten minutes after the water first starts boiling.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You don't turn the 'boiling temp' down because water only boils at 100C/212F (at sea level).&amp;nbsp; You turn the STOVE burner down once the water boils because it helps prevent your kettle from running dry so soon.&amp;nbsp; Reduce the stove setting to the minimum that will keep the water boiling vigorously.&amp;nbsp; Add more water during the cycle if necessary.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next></next>\n<prev>9804383</prev>\n<first>9804191</first>\n<last>9804540</last>\n<when>1234755537</when>\n<utime>02/16/09 05:38 AM</utime>\n</post>"}